Sentencas: Due to their great efficiency, low cost and pollution, and flexible fuel choice, solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have been applied to energy conversion filed.
Titulo: Electrochemical activity of copper doped Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe2O7_ δ cathode catalysts for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, one challenge for developing SOFCs is sluggish oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) rate.
Titulo: Electrochemical activity of copper doped Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe2O7_ δ cathode catalysts for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a series of Ruddlesden-Popper-type Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe2-xCuxO7-delta (SPFCx) oxides are successfully synthesized and thoroughly assessed as potential SOFCs cathodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical activity of copper doped Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe2O7_ δ cathode catalysts for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among all compositions, Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe1.9Cu0.1O7-delta (SPFC10) possesses the best electrocatalysis performance and improved oxygen reduction kinetics, with the lowest polarization resistance (Rp, 0.13 omega cm2) at 700 degrees C. Cu-doping will contribute to improving oxygen transport kinetics, increasing oxygen vacancy concentration, and O 2p band centers close to the Fermi level, hence, enhancing the electrocatalysis performance.
Titulo: Electrochemical activity of copper doped Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe2O7_ δ cathode catalysts for solid oxide fuel cells
